\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Empirical validation of Theorem\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {thm:t5oracle} (T5.1) on TraitGym. Each panel sweeps $K \in \{2, 3, 5, 8, 10, 15, 20, 30\}$ and overlays the bias term $L_F R / K$ (green shaded) and variance term $K / (\pi _{\qopname  \relax m{min}} n)$ (red shaded) of Eq.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {eq:gap_decomp}, plus the T5 bound $G(K) \leq L_F R / K + K / (\pi _{\qopname  \relax m{min}} n)$ (grey curve). Blue dots: empirical mean-cell gap. Red squares: empirical worst-cell gap. The CV-selected $\hat  K_{\mathrm  {CV}}$ (dashed vertical line) coincides with the empirical minimum on both datasets ($\hat  K_{\mathrm  {CV}} = 3$ on Mendelian, $\hat  K_{\mathrm  {CV}} = 2$ on Complex), and the empirical curves track the T5 bound across the bias-dominated and variance-dominated regimes.}}{12}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:k_sweep}{{3}{12}{Empirical validation of Theorem~\ref {thm:t5oracle} (T5.1) on TraitGym. Each panel sweeps $K \in \{2, 3, 5, 8, 10, 15, 20, 30\}$ and overlays the bias term $L_F R / K$ (green shaded) and variance term $K / (\pi _{\min } n)$ (red shaded) of Eq.~\ref {eq:gap_decomp}, plus the T5 bound $G(K) \leq L_F R / K + K / (\pi _{\min } n)$ (grey curve). Blue dots: empirical mean-cell gap. Red squares: empirical worst-cell gap. The CV-selected $\hat K_{\mathrm {CV}}$ (dashed vertical line) coincides with the empirical minimum on both datasets ($\hat K_{\mathrm {CV}} = 3$ on Mendelian, $\hat K_{\mathrm {CV}} = 2$ on Complex), and the empirical curves track the T5 bound across the bias-dominated and variance-dominated regimes}{figure.3}{}}
