\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Head-to-head against off-the-shelf normalized + Mondrian CP, sharing the same $(\hat  {p}, \hat  {\sigma })$. Partition $K$ for B2 / B4 selected per outer fold via proper nested chrom-LOO with $K_{\mathrm  {eval}}$-fair scoring; reporting metric is the $(y, \hat  {\sigma }\text  {-bin})$-conditional worst-cell coverage gap on a fixed $K_{\mathrm  {eval}}$ partition (Mendelian $K_{\mathrm  {eval}} = 3$, Complex $K_{\mathrm  {eval}} = 5$, set per dataset to ensure $\geq 30$ minority-class samples per cell, §\ref  {sec:theory:t5}). Single-seed point estimates. \textbf  {No single-axis CP simultaneously satisfies $\mathrm  {cov}_{|Y=1} \geq 0.85$ and $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin gap $\leq 0.20$ on either dataset.} Of the four variants we evaluated, HCCP is the only frontier point at this corner on both datasets.}}{15}{table.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:h2h}{{4}{15}{Head-to-head against off-the-shelf normalized + Mondrian CP, sharing the same $(\phat , \shat )$. Partition $K$ for B2 / B4 selected per outer fold via proper nested chrom-LOO with $K_{\mathrm {eval}}$-fair scoring; reporting metric is the $(y, \shat \text {-bin})$-conditional worst-cell coverage gap on a fixed $K_{\mathrm {eval}}$ partition (Mendelian $K_{\mathrm {eval}} = 3$, Complex $K_{\mathrm {eval}} = 5$, set per dataset to ensure $\geq 30$ minority-class samples per cell, §\ref {sec:theory:t5}). Single-seed point estimates. \textbf {No single-axis CP simultaneously satisfies $\mathrm {cov}_{|Y=1} \geq 0.85$ and $\shat $-bin gap $\leq 0.20$ on either dataset.} Of the four variants we evaluated, HCCP is the only frontier point at this corner on both datasets}{table.4}{}}
