\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Local coverage by genomic region: per-region coverage minus target $0.90$ across three calibration schemes (Homoscedastic class-conditional / Heteroscedastic split CP / Mondrian-$(y \times \hat  {\sigma }\text  {-bin})$ HCCP). HCCP improves on at-risk regions — e.g., the deeply mis-covered PLS region on Complex ($-0.15$ homoscedastic $\to $ $+0.00$ HCCP) and the over-covered DNase-H3K4me ($+0.07$ $\to $ $-0.03$ HCCP) — while preserving coverage on regions where the simpler schemes already hold. Residual heterogeneity in PLS\_flank ($+0.10$ Mendelian) and DNase-H3K4me ($-0.10$ Complex) reflects local non-stationarity not captured by the global $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin axis; T3-loc (Lem.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {thm:t3loc}) characterises the feature-ball regime that would close these gaps under A3-loc.}}{21}{figure.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:local_heatmap}{{9}{21}{Local coverage by genomic region: per-region coverage minus target $0.90$ across three calibration schemes (Homoscedastic class-conditional / Heteroscedastic split CP / Mondrian-$(y \times \shat \text {-bin})$ HCCP). HCCP improves on at-risk regions — e.g., the deeply mis-covered PLS region on Complex ($-0.15$ homoscedastic $\to $ $+0.00$ HCCP) and the over-covered DNase-H3K4me ($+0.07$ $\to $ $-0.03$ HCCP) — while preserving coverage on regions where the simpler schemes already hold. Residual heterogeneity in PLS\_flank ($+0.10$ Mendelian) and DNase-H3K4me ($-0.10$ Complex) reflects local non-stationarity not captured by the global $\shat $-bin axis; T3-loc (Lem.~\ref {thm:t3loc}) characterises the feature-ball regime that would close these gaps under A3-loc}{figure.9}{}}
