\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces $L_F$ estimator 95\% bootstrap CIs and resulting $K^\star $. LCLS gives a tight CI ($\hat  L_F \approx 3$ Mendelian, $\approx 4.5$ Complex) and a realisable $K^\star $ (22 / 50). Isotonic envelope is loose. Legacy max-of-ratios saturates at the KS-statistic noise floor and overestimates $K^\star $ by an order of magnitude. The modal nested-CV $\hat  K(c_{\mathrm  {outer}}) \in \{5, 8\}$ (Mendelian) and $5$ (Complex) is the binding finite-sample constraint, well below all three asymptotic $K^\star $ predictions.}}{41}{figure.10}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:lf_forest}{{10}{41}{$L_F$ estimator 95\% bootstrap CIs and resulting $K^\star $. LCLS gives a tight CI ($\hat L_F \approx 3$ Mendelian, $\approx 4.5$ Complex) and a realisable $K^\star $ (22 / 50). Isotonic envelope is loose. Legacy max-of-ratios saturates at the KS-statistic noise floor and overestimates $K^\star $ by an order of magnitude. The modal nested-CV $\hat K(c_{\mathrm {outer}}) \in \{5, 8\}$ (Mendelian) and $5$ (Complex) is the binding finite-sample constraint, well below all three asymptotic $K^\star $ predictions}{figure.10}{}}
