\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces Bootstrap distribution of HCCP $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin gap across $B = 200$ chromosome-level resamples. Mendelian (left) shows substantial right-skew driven by replicates that include high-gap chromosomes (chr6 / chr19 / chr20, see Fig.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {fig:per_chrom}); the all-chrom point estimate $0.077$ in Table\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:threeaxis} sits on the right tail of the distribution, while the bootstrap mean $0.020$ is closer to the centre. Complex (right) is much tighter (point estimate and bootstrap mean both $\approx 0.02$). The skew on Mendelian explains the apparent disagreement between Tab.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:main} and Tab.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:threeaxis}.}}{42}{figure.11}\protected@file@percent }
